As someone who placed deals at brokerage firms for twelve years including during the dot com boom I can tell you that this word oversubscribed is completely made up and meaningless
When syndicate managers hear reporters use the term oversubscribed they giggle When they hear an actual number attached like 10 or 220x they cackle at the fing moon
It s actually perfectly priced The bankers raised the maximum they could for the company s use Left nothing on the table
Believe it or not I think has done some really good columns on this subject they might have been around the FB IPO on Business Insider

There will always be a Joe Granville If you re new to financial social media and you see someone speaking with certainty about the future it s easy to fall under a spell It s hard to admit you were tricked so you may even double down at the first sign of humiliation

Granville s paying subs should have gotten off the exit ramp when he switched from stock market buys and sell calls to predicting the next Californian earthquake in 1981 Lots of missed investing opportunity

But tell me something is it anymore absurd to think you can predict an earthquake than it is to say you know what the economy will be doing a year from now Or how commodity prices will be affected Or the SampP 500

Granville a Floridabased economic forecaster and selfstyled soothsayer warned of a huge quake measuring 85 on the Richter ScaleHe also was credited with knocking 238 points off the Dow Jones industrial average earlier this year literally
